cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "DhyutimaanMesh: A Claude-native skill bundle for CAD and meshing in CFD and computational mechanics"
message: "If you use this bundle in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Rahul"
    affiliation: "DhyutiLABS"
repository-code: "https://github.com/DhyutiLABS/DhyutimaanMesh"
url: "https://github.com/DhyutiLABS/DhyutimaanMesh"
abstract: >
  DhyutimaanMesh is a four-skill agentic research bundle for the Claude family of
  large language models, automating CAD-to-mesh workflows for CFD and computational
  mechanics studies. The bundle is method-aware (FEM, FDM, FVM, IBM, overset,
  cut-cell, DG, spectral element), uses only open-source tools (Gmsh, Netgen,
  cfMesh, snappyHexMesh, MMG, TIOGA, AMReX, OpenCASCADE, CadQuery, build123d),
  and enforces falsifiable problem specs with quality envelopes and reference
  comparisons.
keywords:
  - mesh-generation
  - computational-fluid-dynamics
  - finite-element-method
  - finite-volume-method
  - immersed-boundary-method
  - overset-mesh
  - cut-cell
  - cad
  - open-source
  - agentic-research
  - claude
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-06-06"
